**A note on governmental services.**
First, there are virtually no taxes, per-say. All residents of the combs pay for services they use directly. Second, there is very little in the way of insurance, typical banking or finance or investment markets. These things are impractical in a highly mobile and multiplanetary society. Additionally, facilities such as hospitals, nursing homes or large medical facilities are uncommon. Technology has miniaturized enough that the majority of the infrastructure needed for a hospital is unnecessary. A well-equipped ambulance has the majority of the capabilities of a hospital today. Finally, in the case of poor people who are unable to afford medical care or other services typically rendered through social security, there is a large and active church with a monastic culture of people who travel throughout the system and provide free medical and social services for those in need. 
Monastics are actually a large component of the working class above. Over 50% of medical, hospitality, academic, agriculture, public services,; and 70% of cultural workers are actually within monastics or other services offered by the church.




